article.headline: Montana 55, Eastern Wash. 53
article.story: MISSOULA (AP) -- Kevin Criswell hit a 15-foot fadeaway jumper with 3.6 seconds to play Thursday night, lifting the Montana Grizzlies to a 55-53 victory over Eastern Washington. Montana (13-12, 7-5 Big Sky) secured a spot in the conference tournament with the victory. The Eagles (8-18, 5-8) still have a chance to finish in the top six and advance, but will need help from other teams. Matt Dlouhy scored 18 points to lead the Grizzlies, who fell behind 8-0 and trailed much of the game. John Seyfert made 1-of-2 free throws with 1:17 to play to tie the game at 51, then gave Montana a 53-51 lead with 43.8 seconds left on two more foul shots. Marc Axton's free throws with 34.3 seconds remaining tied it again, setting up Criswell's basket. Axton fumbled Eastern's in-bounds pass at halfcourt and was called for over-and-back and the Eagles didn't get off a final shot. Deuce Smith made 8-of-11 field goals and led Eastern with 19 points. Axton added 14. The Eagles' 8-0 lead achieved in the opening 2:14 was the largest of the game for either team. Eastern led 20-19 at halftime. Dlouhy scored 13 of his points over an 8-minute stretch early in the second half as Montana built its largest lead at 38-32 with 10:41 to go. Eastern scored the next 9 points to reclaim a 41-38 lead. Eastern got off 16 more field goal attempts than the Grizzlies, but Montana made 18-of-32 free throws, compared to 5-of-10 for the Eagles.
